body: Most of these types of posts are done by coordinated shills, with the attempt to change the psychology of the readers to drive price action in a certain direction. Big financial institutions try to change market sentiment to maximize their earnings from price swings up or down.   This post just tells me the large firms are about to buy back in, because they are trying to get the price low to make big positions.

author: G-O-K-U
body: This subreddit is for discussing Dogecoin, its price movements, and relevant news—not for personal exit announcements. Posts like these don’t add value to the community. If someone wants to quit crypto and buy a dirt bike, that’s their choice, but why make a dramatic exit post? The market doesn’t care, and neither do most traders.  Instead of flooding the subreddit with posts about leaving, people should focus on discussions that contribute something meaningful—like market trends, analysis, or news about Dogecoin. If every person who sold their holdings made a farewell post, the subreddit would be cluttered with noise instead of useful content.
